00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:10,782 --> 00:00:12,492
<i>You can tell the dead by the look</i>

2
00:00:12,992 --> 00:00:13,952
<i>in their eyes.</i>

3
00:00:24,462 --> 00:00:25,463
<i>That woman…</i>

4
00:00:27,799 --> 00:00:29,342
<i>was definitely dead.</i>

5
00:00:29,425 --> 00:00:31,094
No, we didn't!

6
00:00:32,679 --> 00:00:36,558
I swear we didn't even touch her.
She just died on her own.

7
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:39,894
Chae-ni! Chae…

8
00:00:41,146 --> 00:00:41,980
Chae-ni?

9
00:00:43,064 --> 00:00:44,482
Chae-ni, where did she go?

10
00:00:44,566 --> 00:00:46,276
-Mr. Son!
-She was right here.

11
00:00:46,359 --> 00:00:47,235
<i>But then,</i>

12
00:00:48,194 --> 00:00:49,320
<i>she vanished.</i>

13
00:01:01,875 --> 00:01:04,085
What a load of nonsense. Jeju Island?

14
00:01:04,169 --> 00:01:05,378
That's what I'm seeing.

15
00:01:10,091 --> 00:01:11,926
Yeah, it's definitely showing Jeju.

16
00:01:12,427 --> 00:01:13,928
Maybe Chae-ni's phone is glitchy.

17
00:01:14,012 --> 00:01:15,763
You're the one who's glitchy.

18
00:01:15,847 --> 00:01:19,309
Don't you know she hasn't once
left Haeseong since she was seven?

19
00:01:19,392 --> 00:01:21,561
Yeah, I know. She's the ghost of Haeseong.

20
00:01:21,644 --> 00:01:23,104
But that's what I'm seeing.

21
00:01:23,605 --> 00:01:24,898
Maybe she really is in Jeju.

22
00:01:38,453 --> 00:01:40,246
That silly bear isn't here either.

23
00:01:48,171 --> 00:01:49,631
She packed her things?

24
00:01:55,845 --> 00:01:57,222
SAVINGS ACCOUNT BANKBOOK

25
00:01:59,349 --> 00:02:01,184
DEAREST GRANDMOTHER

26
00:02:08,358 --> 00:02:10,109
Yes, this is Kim Jeon-bok.

27
00:02:10,193 --> 00:02:13,363
I guess it really was glitchy.
It seems to have been an error.

28
00:02:13,446 --> 00:02:15,573
I tried again, and she's in Haeseong.

29
00:02:16,241 --> 00:02:17,283
In the Haedeul-ri area.

30
00:02:24,624 --> 00:02:28,378
And the victim was Ms. Eun Chae-ni,
the granddaughter of Hearty House?

31
00:02:29,003 --> 00:02:29,879
Yes.

32
00:02:30,505 --> 00:02:31,756
I believe so.

33
00:02:32,924 --> 00:02:35,510
Are you talking about that woman
over there?

34
00:02:38,012 --> 00:02:39,973
Yes, that's right.

35
00:02:53,611 --> 00:02:55,488
Isn't that Chae-ni?

36
00:04:06,642 --> 00:04:10,271
THE WONDERFOOLS

37
00:04:11,647 --> 00:04:16,152
EPISODE 2
SECRETS ARE MEANT TO BE KEPT

38
00:04:19,238 --> 00:04:21,699
You reported the disposal
of a dead body, correct?

39
00:04:26,913 --> 00:04:28,915
Deny it, okay?

40
00:04:29,457 --> 00:04:32,293
Deny it, no matter what.
Deny your butt off.

41
00:04:33,002 --> 00:04:34,879
-That's our only way out.
-Okay.

42
00:04:37,757 --> 00:04:41,135
What dead body? Didn't you see earlier
that Eun Chae-ni is fine?

43
00:04:41,219 --> 00:04:44,013
We were staking the place out
and took a tumble, okay?

44
00:04:46,391 --> 00:04:48,476
Check this stink out for yourself!

45
00:04:48,559 --> 00:04:50,353
I've filed countless complaints,

46
00:04:50,436 --> 00:04:53,940
but the only answer I ever get is,
"No, we can't. There's nothing we can do."

47
00:04:54,023 --> 00:04:56,317
You might as well just play a recording.

48
00:05:00,988 --> 00:05:02,031
What else could we do?

49
00:05:02,115 --> 00:05:06,035
Since the authorities wouldn't step up,
we had to catch the dumper ourselves.

50
00:05:08,037 --> 00:05:08,913
What shall we do?

51
00:05:17,130 --> 00:05:18,673
I guess I was mistaken.

52
00:05:20,466 --> 00:05:22,260
Then we'll log this as a false alarm.

53
00:05:23,010 --> 00:05:25,179
Yes. Please do that.

54
00:05:28,474 --> 00:05:29,475
Okay, you can go.

55
00:05:29,559 --> 00:05:31,394
We were going to. Let's go.

56
00:05:32,979 --> 00:05:34,021
Hey, why would you…

57
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,827
What did I tell you?

58
00:05:47,910 --> 00:05:49,662
I said flat-out denial would work.

59
00:05:50,163 --> 00:05:51,789
You can't call it flat-out denial.

60
00:05:51,873 --> 00:05:54,000
I used sound logic to persuade them.

61
00:05:54,083 --> 00:05:56,127
That's the difference between me and you.

62
00:05:56,210 --> 00:05:59,088
An educated person, an uneducated person.

63
00:05:59,172 --> 00:06:01,507
A good person, a no-good person.

64
00:06:02,258 --> 00:06:05,428
A person whose family is filthy rich,
a person who is dirt poor.

65
00:06:06,262 --> 00:06:07,263
Damn it.

66
00:06:08,347 --> 00:06:10,433
Hey, but are you really okay?

67
00:06:10,933 --> 00:06:13,936
I totally thought you were dead.
Why weren't you breathing?

68
00:06:14,020 --> 00:06:16,189
I thought I was dead too.

69
00:06:17,190 --> 00:06:18,900
I even saw some weird stuff.

70
00:06:18,983 --> 00:06:20,318
<i>What ye doin' o'er there?</i>

71
00:06:21,402 --> 00:06:23,613
Don't loaf around and get outta there.

72
00:06:23,696 --> 00:06:26,866
<i>She kept saying things</i>
<i>that I couldn't understand.</i>

73
00:06:26,949 --> 00:06:30,328
Ain't ye hearin' me?
I said scoot on outta there!

74
00:06:30,411 --> 00:06:34,040
The wind's kickin' up real bad.
At this rate, you ain't gettin' out alone.

75
00:06:34,123 --> 00:06:37,126
Can't ye hear me?
I'm tellin' ya, it's mighty dicey!

76
00:06:37,210 --> 00:06:39,795
What ye doin'? Get outta there already!

77
00:06:41,464 --> 00:06:43,382
Maybe you had a near-death experience.

78
00:06:43,466 --> 00:06:45,218
You know, not actually dying,

79
00:06:45,301 --> 00:06:48,304
but just dipping your toes
into the afterlife.

80
00:06:50,223 --> 00:06:51,974
Maybe you saw a grim reaper!

81
00:06:52,058 --> 00:06:53,392
You think so?

82
00:06:54,602 --> 00:06:56,646
So was I dead or not?

83
00:06:57,730 --> 00:06:58,898
Maybe I half-died.

84
00:07:00,149 --> 00:07:02,235
Like a half-dried squid or something?

85
00:07:03,069 --> 00:07:05,488
Does your grandma know
the shape you're in?

86
00:07:06,322 --> 00:07:08,032
Of course she doesn't.

87
00:07:08,115 --> 00:07:09,909
If she did, she'd lose it.

88
00:07:09,992 --> 00:07:11,702
Don't you know what she's like?

89
00:07:11,786 --> 00:07:14,330
The big cheese of Myeong-dong,
King Jeon-bok.

90
00:07:15,623 --> 00:07:16,707
If she finds out…

91
00:07:16,791 --> 00:07:17,959
If she finds out?

92
00:07:18,292 --> 00:07:19,460
EUN CHAE-NI'S

93
00:07:19,544 --> 00:07:20,795
KIDNAPPERS

94
00:07:26,217 --> 00:07:28,302
We're truly sorry, ma'am.

95
00:07:31,722 --> 00:07:32,932
Go on and bury them.

96
00:07:33,015 --> 00:07:34,392
Yes, ma'am!

97
00:07:34,475 --> 00:07:36,561
Please don't do that!

98
00:07:39,855 --> 00:07:40,815
Hold it!

99
00:07:42,692 --> 00:07:44,569
Why are you over there, not here with us?

100
00:07:46,571 --> 00:07:49,240
What was that word
I told you to memorize again?

101
00:07:49,323 --> 00:07:52,159
How diplomats
get away with crimes overseas.

102
00:07:52,243 --> 00:07:55,204
-Immunity.
-That's it. Granddaughter immunity.

103
00:07:56,205 --> 00:07:58,374
Is there no
granddaughter's friend immunity?

104
00:07:58,457 --> 00:07:59,500
What do I do now?

105
00:07:59,584 --> 00:08:01,544
Hey, Mr. Son, what should we do?

106
00:08:01,627 --> 00:08:04,630
Why did you rope us into this?
You could've just stolen the money.

107
00:08:04,714 --> 00:08:07,341
It's okay.
We'll make sure we don't get caught.

108
00:08:07,425 --> 00:08:08,759
Flat-out denial always works.

109
00:08:08,843 --> 00:08:10,886
You think denial will cut it?

110
00:08:10,970 --> 00:08:12,555
Is that the best you can do?

111
00:08:12,638 --> 00:08:14,473
Who said you'll just deny it?

112
00:08:15,641 --> 00:08:17,727
Deny with passion, with all you've got.

113
00:08:19,979 --> 00:08:23,024
Would that actually work?
Then we'd be in the clear, right?

114
00:08:23,107 --> 00:08:25,568
Of course. Nothing beats flat-out denial.

115
00:08:29,614 --> 00:08:30,573
Did you really

116
00:08:30,656 --> 00:08:34,160
think this plan through carefully?

117
00:08:34,660 --> 00:08:36,537
How would you have gotten the 50 million?

118
00:08:36,621 --> 00:08:38,122
Wired to my account, of course.

119
00:08:38,623 --> 00:08:40,499
Borrowed accounts are illegal, you know.

120
00:08:45,129 --> 00:08:48,633
I had no clue because I'd never
talked to you long enough.

121
00:08:49,175 --> 00:08:52,845
That you were a girl
with such an empty head.

122
00:08:52,928 --> 00:08:55,181
To think I trusted bozos like you

123
00:08:55,723 --> 00:08:58,893
and co-conspired to get 50 million won…

124
00:08:58,976 --> 00:09:00,436
-Want some?
-What are they?

125
00:09:02,521 --> 00:09:03,814
-These are good.
-Right?

126
00:09:03,898 --> 00:09:05,566
Hey, I'm talking to you!

127
00:09:15,743 --> 00:09:18,412
This is my fault. It's all my fault.

128
00:09:18,496 --> 00:09:22,833
I, a Homo sapiens who conspired
with Neanderthals, am to blame.

129
00:09:24,126 --> 00:09:24,960
If I ever

130
00:09:25,461 --> 00:09:29,090
get involved in another ridiculous
fake kidnapping of Eun Chae-ni

131
00:09:29,173 --> 00:09:32,093
or another half-dried squid
near-death experience,

132
00:09:32,176 --> 00:09:33,928
you can consider me…

133
00:09:34,011 --> 00:09:34,970
Screwed.

134
00:09:41,769 --> 00:09:42,812
She heard.

135
00:09:43,396 --> 00:09:44,230
Everything.

136
00:10:00,830 --> 00:10:02,164
Run!

137
00:10:15,094 --> 00:10:18,347
You know the crimes you are guilty of!

138
00:10:20,850 --> 00:10:23,269
Punish him mercilessly!

139
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:33,320
I am innocent. Treason, of all crimes?

140
00:10:33,404 --> 00:10:35,781
This is preposterous.

141
00:10:36,490 --> 00:10:38,492
I truly am innocent.

142
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:43,873
I swear to the heavens above
that I have not one speck of shame.

143
00:10:43,956 --> 00:10:45,082
How dare you!

144
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:49,795
Twist his legs until he confesses!

145
00:10:54,258 --> 00:10:57,136
I have done no wrong!

146
00:11:10,941 --> 00:11:12,818
Is this thing really glitching?

147
00:11:15,863 --> 00:11:16,781
Come out.

148
00:11:19,283 --> 00:11:21,160
Come here
before I get people to drag you out!

149
00:11:25,790 --> 00:11:28,584
Ms. Kim…

150
00:11:30,503 --> 00:11:32,129
Could you please move…

151
00:11:35,633 --> 00:11:37,426
That… No, it's okay.

152
00:11:37,510 --> 00:11:38,844
Thank you.

153
00:11:40,054 --> 00:11:44,350
Just moving one of your legs
is more than enough for me to get out.

154
00:11:44,433 --> 00:11:45,518
Like this.

155
00:11:55,152 --> 00:11:57,822
-You must be furious.
-I tried to talk her out of it.

156
00:11:57,905 --> 00:12:01,158
-But it was all Chae-ni's plan.
-I said, "Think about your grandma."

157
00:12:01,242 --> 00:12:03,994
-She said we'd get five million each--
-I really tried--

158
00:12:05,955 --> 00:12:08,916
In other words, the three of you

159
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:12,211
staged a kidnapping for money?

160
00:12:12,294 --> 00:12:16,799
-I wouldn't quite put it like that.
-Mr. Son here wouldn't fix my roof.

161
00:12:16,882 --> 00:12:19,426
-Chae-ni planned all of this--
-I just wanted my roof--

162
00:12:21,846 --> 00:12:23,264
Where's your mastermind, Eunie?

163
00:12:23,347 --> 00:12:26,934
That's exactly it!
Eun Chae-ni is the mastermind, Ms. Kim.

164
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:30,980
Eunie.

165
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:35,484
Your accomplices have already betrayed you
without hesitation. Get out here.

166
00:12:39,238 --> 00:12:42,867
Why, you always make
things worse for yourself!

167
00:12:43,450 --> 00:12:44,660
Get out here!

168
00:12:48,247 --> 00:12:49,164
What?

169
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:52,960
I definitely saw her climb in here.

170
00:12:57,172 --> 00:12:58,591
Where were you hiding?

171
00:12:59,550 --> 00:13:00,384
Grandma.

172
00:13:02,428 --> 00:13:03,345
Can you see me?

173
00:13:03,429 --> 00:13:05,931
What newfangled nonsense is this?

174
00:13:06,015 --> 00:13:08,559
Did you think I wouldn't be able
to see you? Get out now!

175
00:13:10,394 --> 00:13:11,395
Deary me.

176
00:13:11,478 --> 00:13:12,897
What do I do, Grandma?

177
00:13:14,148 --> 00:13:16,525
Something must be really wrong with me.

178
00:13:17,109 --> 00:13:20,404
I keep seeing things. What do I do?

179
00:13:20,487 --> 00:13:21,530
How?

180
00:13:22,031 --> 00:13:25,242
What feels wrong? How?
Should I call the hospital director?

181
00:13:25,326 --> 00:13:27,661
-I don't know.
-Are you running a fever?

182
00:13:28,203 --> 00:13:29,246
-Oh dear.
-I just…

183
00:13:31,206 --> 00:13:34,710
Would you look at that?
She's using her granddaughter immunity.

184
00:13:36,921 --> 00:13:37,963
Tell me what happened.

185
00:13:38,047 --> 00:13:40,758
-Just now, I was in some weird…
-Yes, what is it?

186
00:13:40,841 --> 00:13:42,968
-Yes?
-Grandma!

187
00:13:43,052 --> 00:13:45,512
Breathe. Just breathe. And sit down.

188
00:13:45,596 --> 00:13:48,557
Sit right here and take a deep breath.

189
00:13:49,058 --> 00:13:50,851
Just take a breath.

190
00:13:52,853 --> 00:13:53,771
He's annoying.

191
00:13:53,854 --> 00:13:55,981
He's annoying? That's no good.

192
00:13:56,065 --> 00:13:57,733
Hey, you're annoying her!

193
00:14:00,653 --> 00:14:02,363
<i>You're looking for someone?</i>

194
00:14:03,656 --> 00:14:04,531
Who?

195
00:14:05,157 --> 00:14:06,617
The Child of Eternity?

196
00:14:08,994 --> 00:14:10,079
I don't know.

197
00:14:11,914 --> 00:14:16,043
There <i>were </i>some children
who survived the fire back then.

198
00:14:17,962 --> 00:14:21,507
But I'm not sure about
this Child of Eternity you speak of.

199
00:14:25,010 --> 00:14:31,183
Oh, but I do remember
one other child very clearly.

200
00:14:32,309 --> 00:14:33,894
Number 3972.

201
00:14:35,604 --> 00:14:37,648
Because I saved him

202
00:14:38,816 --> 00:14:40,818
from the fire that day.

203
00:14:47,032 --> 00:14:49,201
Sir!

204
00:14:49,284 --> 00:14:51,245
Please open this door!

205
00:14:51,745 --> 00:14:53,622
Please open this door!

206
00:14:58,168 --> 00:14:59,503
<i>Number 3972?</i>

207
00:14:59,586 --> 00:15:01,880
You saved that child?

208
00:15:01,964 --> 00:15:04,842
Yes, I sure did.

209
00:15:06,844 --> 00:15:08,262
And that child

210
00:15:09,471 --> 00:15:11,390
has returned to Haeseong.

211
00:15:13,726 --> 00:15:15,602
He's grown into a fine young man.

212
00:15:15,686 --> 00:15:18,147
He didn't seem to recognize me,

213
00:15:18,647 --> 00:15:21,483
but I recognized him right away.

214
00:15:21,984 --> 00:15:23,485
Number 3972.

215
00:15:25,070 --> 00:15:26,822
I'm certain it's him.

216
00:15:28,198 --> 00:15:29,324
I see.

217
00:15:29,825 --> 00:15:31,535
Thank you for telling me.

218
00:15:32,411 --> 00:15:34,204
Here, eat up before it gets cold.

219
00:15:56,185 --> 00:15:59,313
I don't know how many years it's been

220
00:15:59,396 --> 00:16:01,690
since I sat across from you like this…

221
00:16:03,567 --> 00:16:05,736
and ate a hot meal.

222
00:16:11,366 --> 00:16:13,160
After you died,

223
00:16:14,536 --> 00:16:17,748
I was sure a day like this
would never come again.

224
00:16:20,709 --> 00:16:23,587
I'm so glad you're here.

225
00:16:36,558 --> 00:16:39,103
Did you hear that? Number 3972.

226
00:16:45,234 --> 00:16:46,193
Honey.

227
00:16:48,987 --> 00:16:50,280
Honey!

228
00:16:50,864 --> 00:16:53,992
Where… where am I?

229
00:16:54,743 --> 00:16:55,744
Honey?

230
00:17:05,003 --> 00:17:06,255
NUMBER 3972
ABILITY: TELEKINESIS

231
00:17:06,338 --> 00:17:08,048
What is all this?

232
00:18:19,036 --> 00:18:21,288
Don't you have a family?

233
00:18:23,707 --> 00:18:24,708
I don't know.

234
00:18:25,876 --> 00:18:27,586
I can't remember.

235
00:18:28,462 --> 00:18:29,880
Not even your mom's face?

236
00:18:30,547 --> 00:18:31,590
Or your dad's?

237
00:19:36,154 --> 00:19:37,072
Don't worry.

238
00:19:37,572 --> 00:19:38,865
I can't die.

239
00:19:39,658 --> 00:19:41,785
You can't die?

240
00:19:52,045 --> 00:19:55,340
Focus and try again. You can do it.

241
00:20:39,885 --> 00:20:41,011
How did he do that?

242
00:20:42,262 --> 00:20:43,764
That's awesome.

243
00:21:07,245 --> 00:21:09,081
Stop!

244
00:21:42,114 --> 00:21:44,032
You're still doing this, City Hall guy?

245
00:21:44,116 --> 00:21:46,410
I asked you
to please keep it down at night!

246
00:21:46,910 --> 00:21:48,620
You're really trying my patience.

247
00:21:49,121 --> 00:21:51,039
Knock it off or move out already!

248
00:21:53,583 --> 00:21:55,877
<i>I can't die.</i>

249
00:21:59,381 --> 00:22:00,924
<i>But that kid was definitely</i>

250
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,093
<i>a boy.</i>

251
00:22:53,018 --> 00:22:53,935
What…

252
00:22:55,103 --> 00:22:55,937
Huh?

253
00:22:57,689 --> 00:22:58,607
How?

254
00:23:00,984 --> 00:23:02,569
Why, what is it?

255
00:23:02,652 --> 00:23:04,988
Is something wrong? Is it very serious?

256
00:23:05,071 --> 00:23:06,531
Well, it's…

257
00:23:07,991 --> 00:23:11,244
I'm ready for anything, so just tell me.

258
00:23:11,328 --> 00:23:12,412
Spit it out!

259
00:23:13,622 --> 00:23:14,831
Well,

260
00:23:15,415 --> 00:23:16,249
it's very…

261
00:23:17,751 --> 00:23:20,962
I don't quite understand
how this has happened either,

262
00:23:21,046 --> 00:23:22,839
but the test results are…

263
00:23:22,923 --> 00:23:24,549
Everything here

264
00:23:26,051 --> 00:23:26,927
looks normal.

265
00:23:28,094 --> 00:23:28,929
Come again?

266
00:23:29,012 --> 00:23:32,224
If you look at the graphs here,

267
00:23:32,307 --> 00:23:35,644
you can see they're all very stable
with no major fluctuations.

268
00:23:35,727 --> 00:23:37,395
This is from last time. This is now.

269
00:23:38,021 --> 00:23:40,357
I checked the ultrasound results, too,

270
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,150
and her kidneys look clean.

271
00:23:42,234 --> 00:23:45,237
Even the valvular inflammation
I saw last time is completely gone.

272
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:49,115
And this is the X-ray we just took.
That one's from last time.

273
00:23:49,199 --> 00:23:51,034
Her lungs have cleared up too.

274
00:23:51,117 --> 00:23:52,994
Last time, her heart was this big,

275
00:23:53,578 --> 00:23:54,621
but now,

276
00:23:55,372 --> 00:23:57,832
it's back to a completely normal size.

277
00:23:57,916 --> 00:23:59,376
So, you're saying…

278
00:24:01,545 --> 00:24:04,047
To get this straight,

279
00:24:05,382 --> 00:24:06,800
you seem to be saying

280
00:24:07,300 --> 00:24:09,052
that everything has improved.

281
00:24:09,553 --> 00:24:11,096
Would that be right?

282
00:24:11,179 --> 00:24:13,557
No, ma'am, it's not just an improvement.

283
00:24:15,350 --> 00:24:16,476
She's in

284
00:24:17,060 --> 00:24:18,311
perfect health.

285
00:24:19,729 --> 00:24:20,564
How?

286
00:24:20,647 --> 00:24:23,483
Exactly! I've never seen
anything like this before.

287
00:24:23,567 --> 00:24:26,987
Of course, once in a blue moon,
things like this do happen,

288
00:24:27,070 --> 00:24:28,863
and there's no telling why.

289
00:24:28,947 --> 00:24:31,491
We usually call them miracles.

290
00:24:33,368 --> 00:24:34,911
I think, ma'am, that Chae-ni

291
00:24:35,620 --> 00:24:37,330
has been blessed with a miracle.

292
00:24:40,292 --> 00:24:41,209
A miracle?

293
00:24:41,835 --> 00:24:43,920
<i>This child is a miracle child.</i>

294
00:25:31,176 --> 00:25:35,138
CHOI YEONG-JUN

295
00:25:46,191 --> 00:25:49,110
<i>This is Choi Yeong-jun.</i>
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

296
00:25:49,611 --> 00:25:51,363
Hello, Director Choi. It's me.

297
00:25:52,238 --> 00:25:54,032
King Jeon-bok of Myeong-dong.

298
00:25:54,574 --> 00:25:56,368
Call me when you get this.

299
00:26:06,211 --> 00:26:09,214
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION

300
00:26:09,297 --> 00:26:11,508
APOCALYPSE ON DECEMBER 31ST

301
00:26:11,591 --> 00:26:15,053
RECEIVE SALVATION
AND BE GRANTED ETERNAL LIFE

302
00:26:22,686 --> 00:26:25,563
APOCALYPSE
SALVATION

303
00:26:33,571 --> 00:26:35,156
What do we do now, Mr. Son?

304
00:26:35,657 --> 00:26:38,284
How will we ever face Ms. Kim now?

305
00:26:38,785 --> 00:26:39,911
You tell me.

306
00:26:40,412 --> 00:26:43,748
I refused, but you two insisted on
roping me into this. So tell me.

307
00:26:44,457 --> 00:26:45,542
Mr. Son.

308
00:26:46,042 --> 00:26:49,379
If you hadn't assumed Chae-ni was dead,
we wouldn't be in this mess.

309
00:26:50,046 --> 00:26:50,880
Assumed?

310
00:26:51,506 --> 00:26:52,340
Listen.

311
00:26:52,966 --> 00:26:54,759
She was definitely dead.

312
00:26:54,843 --> 00:26:56,386
She didn't have a pulse.

313
00:26:56,469 --> 00:26:59,180
How could a dead person come back to life?

314
00:26:59,264 --> 00:27:02,392
You went as far as to dispose of
a perfectly healthy person in the hills.

315
00:27:02,475 --> 00:27:04,728
Quiet. Temporarily laid to rest,
not disposed of.

316
00:27:05,812 --> 00:27:07,397
Besides, did I act alone?

317
00:27:07,480 --> 00:27:08,940
You're even worse than I am.

318
00:27:09,023 --> 00:27:12,444
How could you, her friend,
dump her body in a garbage pit?

319
00:27:15,989 --> 00:27:17,031
Mr. Son!

320
00:27:17,532 --> 00:27:20,201
That's why I said we shouldn't do it.

321
00:27:20,285 --> 00:27:23,580
Of course, there it is!
There go the waterworks again.

322
00:27:23,663 --> 00:27:27,917
You look like a thug,
but you cry and sulk at the drop of a hat!

323
00:27:28,001 --> 00:27:30,837
Do you know how ghastly
your crying face is?

324
00:27:31,796 --> 00:27:34,841
Don't make fun of people's looks.
You shouldn't do that.

325
00:27:34,924 --> 00:27:37,427
Do you think I'm making fun of your looks?

326
00:27:37,510 --> 00:27:38,762
I'm not.

327
00:27:39,679 --> 00:27:41,514
Wait, you weren't? Really?

328
00:27:41,598 --> 00:27:43,433
Of course not.

329
00:27:43,516 --> 00:27:47,145
I was going for a double whammy
by making fun of your looks <i>and </i>sulkiness.

330
00:27:47,228 --> 00:27:48,605
Get a clue, Sappy Sap.

331
00:27:48,688 --> 00:27:50,899
With your runny nose.
God, you drive me nuts.

332
00:28:15,381 --> 00:28:17,467
I told you not to drink from the bottle.

333
00:28:22,889 --> 00:28:23,848
By the way,

334
00:28:24,349 --> 00:28:26,935
any news about the illegal dumping
in the hills?

335
00:28:27,018 --> 00:28:27,852
What?

336
00:28:28,353 --> 00:28:29,437
Right, that.

337
00:28:29,521 --> 00:28:32,357
I actually went earlier
and gave them a good talking-to.

338
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:34,108
Any time now. Don't worry.

339
00:28:35,193 --> 00:28:36,152
And your mother?

340
00:28:37,362 --> 00:28:38,196
What?

341
00:28:38,279 --> 00:28:40,114
Did you make it clear to her

342
00:28:40,198 --> 00:28:43,451
that we're not sending her to Hawaii
but the Hawaii Resort in Bugok?

343
00:28:45,537 --> 00:28:49,082
Yeah, that. Well, you know…

344
00:28:50,083 --> 00:28:52,669
She knows our situation, after all.

345
00:28:53,503 --> 00:28:55,421
She didn't seem too disappointed.

346
00:29:14,524 --> 00:29:16,693
What are you even doing?

347
00:29:17,235 --> 00:29:19,153
I just have some things to think about.

348
00:29:19,237 --> 00:29:20,572
Do you have to do it there?

349
00:29:20,655 --> 00:29:22,907
Yeah, I have to do it here.

350
00:29:24,033 --> 00:29:25,285
Well, I'm going to bed.

351
00:29:25,368 --> 00:29:27,120
Okay, good night, Ms. Moon Mi-hui.

352
00:29:45,430 --> 00:29:49,392
Here comes my daughter, Cheong,
just as I was opening the fridge door.

353
00:29:51,769 --> 00:29:53,229
Want some ice to cool down?

354
00:29:57,942 --> 00:29:58,776
So that's a no?

355
00:30:03,823 --> 00:30:05,867
Are you the problem or am I?

356
00:30:05,950 --> 00:30:09,662
If you are, I can call for a repair,
but who do I call if I'm the problem?

357
00:30:27,764 --> 00:30:29,223
How can this…

358
00:30:32,852 --> 00:30:33,728
How…

359
00:31:30,034 --> 00:31:31,744
Who exactly were your accomplices?

360
00:31:37,917 --> 00:31:38,960
I acted alone.

361
00:31:39,043 --> 00:31:40,962
Ro-bin and Sonie from the flower shop.

362
00:31:41,045 --> 00:31:43,006
I know those two idiots were involved.

363
00:31:43,756 --> 00:31:45,008
Was there anyone else?

364
00:31:45,717 --> 00:31:48,594
I told you. The three of us acted alone.

365
00:31:50,722 --> 00:31:52,473
Do you not know what "alone" means?

366
00:31:53,975 --> 00:31:56,602
I sure do. I know very well.

367
00:31:58,563 --> 00:32:00,648
The soup's getting cold. Eat.

368
00:32:03,735 --> 00:32:07,363
How did you even plan to travel
without a passport?

369
00:32:15,705 --> 00:32:18,291
What did the doctor say?

370
00:32:19,375 --> 00:32:22,587
Did he give you some bad news?

371
00:32:23,796 --> 00:32:25,339
While you were growing up,

372
00:32:25,923 --> 00:32:28,009
there wasn't a day that I didn't pray

373
00:32:29,218 --> 00:32:31,304
nor a single day I had peace of mind.

374
00:32:31,971 --> 00:32:35,433
If I couldn't reach you for just a moment,
my heart would sink.

375
00:32:35,516 --> 00:32:38,770
Every time I took you to the hospital,
my blood ran cold.

376
00:32:40,772 --> 00:32:42,440
That's how scared I've been

377
00:32:43,357 --> 00:32:44,358
for the past 20 years.

378
00:32:47,737 --> 00:32:48,863
But

379
00:32:50,406 --> 00:32:52,366
no matter how scared I was…

380
00:32:54,327 --> 00:32:55,745
I doubt I was as scared as you.

381
00:33:04,378 --> 00:33:05,505
I'm sorry, Grandma.

382
00:33:06,964 --> 00:33:08,591
What are you sorry for?

383
00:33:08,674 --> 00:33:11,803
You've made me
the happiest I've been in 27 years.

384
00:33:13,679 --> 00:33:16,140
The test results were excellent.

385
00:33:16,808 --> 00:33:18,726
He said everything's normal.

386
00:33:19,393 --> 00:33:21,395
I never thought I'd see this day.

387
00:33:21,479 --> 00:33:23,481
You're as clean as a whistle.

388
00:33:23,564 --> 00:33:26,567
The size, shape, and condition
of your heart are all perfect.

389
00:33:26,651 --> 00:33:28,027
Why, that doctor

390
00:33:28,528 --> 00:33:31,572
made a huge fuss, calling it a miracle.

391
00:33:34,617 --> 00:33:35,868
So,

392
00:33:36,828 --> 00:33:37,829
from now on,

393
00:33:38,913 --> 00:33:41,207
live your life to the fullest, okay?

394
00:33:42,250 --> 00:33:45,211
But don't let your guard down
and get regular checkups.

395
00:33:45,294 --> 00:33:46,295
What was it, again?

396
00:33:46,796 --> 00:33:50,174
Go see the northern lights or whatever
and that huge-headed rock.

397
00:33:50,842 --> 00:33:54,011
And what was it?
Go see the Iguana Falls or whatever.

398
00:33:54,095 --> 00:33:55,638
And go explore Africa.

399
00:33:56,514 --> 00:33:57,723
You should do it all.

400
00:33:59,392 --> 00:34:00,434
So,

401
00:34:00,518 --> 00:34:01,936
from now on,

402
00:34:02,812 --> 00:34:04,522
live life to the fullest, okay?

403
00:34:05,982 --> 00:34:07,483
Make the darn most of it,

404
00:34:09,110 --> 00:34:10,528
and pay for your own trips.

405
00:34:19,662 --> 00:34:22,665
How will I ever earn enough
peeling onions?

406
00:34:38,222 --> 00:34:39,098
Grandma!

407
00:34:42,143 --> 00:34:43,394
Before that…

408
00:34:46,564 --> 00:34:47,398
REWARD GRAPES

409
00:34:47,481 --> 00:34:48,733
…you need to fill this up.

410
00:34:49,984 --> 00:34:50,943
Until then,

411
00:34:51,444 --> 00:34:54,488
be good, stay healthy, and speak politely.

412
00:34:54,572 --> 00:34:57,825
And don't spit on other people's houses.
Then I'll give these to you.

413
00:34:59,577 --> 00:35:03,414
Come on, Grandma. I'm not seven.

414
00:35:03,497 --> 00:35:05,249
I'm 27 years old.

415
00:35:05,333 --> 00:35:07,293
If you don't like it, best get peeling.

416
00:35:07,376 --> 00:35:08,711
Oh no.

417
00:35:12,298 --> 00:35:13,341
All right.

418
00:35:14,967 --> 00:35:17,011
First, eat all your food.

419
00:35:35,196 --> 00:35:38,699
Yes, this is Kim Jeon-bok of Hearty House.

420
00:35:47,625 --> 00:35:49,377
It's been a while, Director Choi.

421
00:36:08,980 --> 00:36:10,273
"Great job."

422
00:36:18,698 --> 00:36:20,658
No more purple lips.

423
00:36:22,618 --> 00:36:24,120
No more dull skin.

424
00:36:26,122 --> 00:36:27,581
No more tinnitus.

425
00:36:29,166 --> 00:36:30,209
And no more bruises.

426
00:36:33,796 --> 00:36:35,715
Even my heart's beating fine.

427
00:36:37,675 --> 00:36:41,012
There's been a definite improvement
since my near-death experience.

428
00:36:42,638 --> 00:36:44,473
So why do I keep seeing things?

429
00:36:44,557 --> 00:36:47,351
What ye doin'? Get outta there already!

430
00:36:49,020 --> 00:36:50,187
But that place

431
00:36:51,188 --> 00:36:52,773
wasn't even a tunnel.

432
00:37:00,489 --> 00:37:01,782
Could it be time…

433
00:37:02,283 --> 00:37:04,618
<i>I can't even bring myself</i>
<i>to say "time travel."</i>

434
00:37:10,875 --> 00:37:12,043
<i>That's right.</i>

435
00:37:12,543 --> 00:37:15,880
<i>My brain must have been</i>
<i>deprived of oxygen for a long time.</i>

436
00:37:16,380 --> 00:37:18,174
<i>That's for certain.</i>

437
00:37:24,638 --> 00:37:26,724
<i>There's no doubt they were hallucinations.</i>

438
00:37:27,224 --> 00:37:28,142
<i>Wait a minute.</i>

439
00:37:28,726 --> 00:37:30,978
<i>Then in exchange for a working heart…</i>

440
00:37:31,812 --> 00:37:34,315
<i>7 times 5 is 35, 7 times 6 is 42,</i>
<i>7 times 7 is 49…</i>

441
00:37:34,398 --> 00:37:37,234
<i>-7 times 8 is…</i>
-Don't touch your eyes, idiot!

442
00:37:41,155 --> 00:37:44,533
<i>Did I lose my brain</i>
<i>in exchange for a working heart?</i>

443
00:37:46,744 --> 00:37:49,121
-This can't be.
-Chae-ni, you have a guest outside.

444
00:37:49,205 --> 00:37:50,414
It's a guy.

445
00:37:50,498 --> 00:37:52,166
He's a looker.

446
00:37:53,167 --> 00:37:54,835
Don't touch your eyes. It stings.

447
00:37:55,753 --> 00:37:56,587
Don't move.

448
00:38:01,092 --> 00:38:02,218
Why are you here?

449
00:38:02,718 --> 00:38:04,053
What do you want from me?

450
00:38:04,845 --> 00:38:05,888
Here to pay up?

451
00:38:08,140 --> 00:38:09,350
How many times have you died?

452
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:15,314
Me?

453
00:38:15,398 --> 00:38:17,108
Was that the first time?

454
00:38:17,817 --> 00:38:19,151
Or have you died before?

455
00:38:22,321 --> 00:38:24,573
Is he saying he wants to die?

456
00:38:24,657 --> 00:38:26,659
No. That's him.

457
00:38:26,742 --> 00:38:28,661
The guy who reported us
for dumping a body.

458
00:38:28,744 --> 00:38:31,080
When you had
that near-death experience yesterday.

459
00:38:31,163 --> 00:38:32,832
I see.

460
00:38:33,332 --> 00:38:37,086
First, you wreck my suitcase,
then you make a big fuss over nothing?

461
00:38:37,169 --> 00:38:40,673
I reported it for your sake.
So they could at least find your body.

462
00:38:40,756 --> 00:38:42,216
My body?

463
00:38:42,299 --> 00:38:44,385
I'm standing right here, alive and well!

464
00:38:44,468 --> 00:38:46,595
-You were definitely dead.
-No, I wasn't!

465
00:38:46,679 --> 00:38:49,432
You're making me sound like
some kind of freak.

466
00:38:50,057 --> 00:38:50,933
So what happened?

467
00:38:54,895 --> 00:38:55,938
It's a secret.

468
00:38:58,441 --> 00:39:00,359
<i>She's definitely hiding something.</i>

469
00:39:00,943 --> 00:39:02,236
So you can't tell me?

470
00:39:03,863 --> 00:39:05,781
It's a secret because I can't tell you.

471
00:39:05,865 --> 00:39:08,284
It wouldn't be a secret
if I could tell you, would it?

472
00:39:15,207 --> 00:39:16,333
Then, have you ever…

473
00:39:24,133 --> 00:39:25,301
heard of Wunderkinder?

474
00:39:27,094 --> 00:39:28,220
What's this

475
00:39:28,762 --> 00:39:31,474
Boon… the King Duck?

476
00:39:31,974 --> 00:39:33,142
I don't even like duck.

477
00:39:34,018 --> 00:39:35,728
Is it a new duck joint or something?

478
00:39:35,811 --> 00:39:39,857
Why do you keep bothering us?
We told you that nothing happened.

479
00:39:39,940 --> 00:39:41,650
See? Nothing happened.

480
00:39:45,571 --> 00:39:46,739
Well, okay, then.

481
00:39:47,281 --> 00:39:48,449
If you say so.

482
00:39:58,501 --> 00:40:01,086
What was that?
We've got ourselves a nutjob, right?

483
00:40:01,170 --> 00:40:03,464
What if he finds out about the kidnapping?

484
00:40:03,547 --> 00:40:04,924
It was my idea anyway.

485
00:40:05,841 --> 00:40:09,512
But Mr. Son said we could be in trouble
if the police find out!

486
00:40:09,595 --> 00:40:11,388
They'd have no evidence anyway.

487
00:40:13,933 --> 00:40:16,936
You grabbed my suitcase
and camcorder, didn't you?

488
00:40:17,811 --> 00:40:20,606
No. They're probably still
in the abandoned greenhouse.

489
00:40:21,982 --> 00:40:23,400
You didn't delete the footage?

490
00:40:24,151 --> 00:40:25,402
No.

491
00:40:25,486 --> 00:40:27,613
You died,
and we were so freaked out that--

492
00:40:28,906 --> 00:40:30,533
Oh, for God's sake!

493
00:40:30,616 --> 00:40:32,993
You're peeling my share
of the onions for today.

494
00:40:33,077 --> 00:40:35,996
And tomorrow and the day after that
and after that! All yours!

495
00:40:44,838 --> 00:40:47,299
Mr. Son? It's Ro-bin.

496
00:40:48,259 --> 00:40:49,677
Okay, goober. Talk later.

497
00:40:53,681 --> 00:40:56,308
I knew I shouldn't have gotten mixed up
with those bozos.

498
00:40:57,643 --> 00:40:59,478
Everything's going sideways.

499
00:41:03,524 --> 00:41:06,777
Please, Rala.
Why are you giving me a hard time too?

500
00:41:11,365 --> 00:41:12,825
That's it, you beauty.

501
00:41:35,055 --> 00:41:38,934
Okay, your turn for lunch.
Today's menu is <i>jjajangbap</i>. Go eat.

502
00:41:39,018 --> 00:41:41,604
Un-jeong, you should also…
You're already gone.

503
00:41:41,687 --> 00:41:45,399
He went alone again, that brat.

504
00:41:45,482 --> 00:41:46,609
Oh boy.

505
00:41:53,115 --> 00:41:55,951
<i>There's only one way to find out for sure</i>
<i>if she possesses</i>

506
00:41:56,452 --> 00:41:57,995
<i>the ability to resurrect.</i>

507
00:41:59,330 --> 00:42:01,290
<i>Make her need to revive herself.</i>

508
00:42:47,002 --> 00:42:47,878
Extra crispy.

509
00:43:27,835 --> 00:43:29,253
<i>But what if</i>

510
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:30,754
<i>I'm wrong?</i>

511
00:43:53,861 --> 00:43:54,778
Excuse me.

512
00:44:09,501 --> 00:44:14,757
HAEWON FLOWERS

513
00:44:35,778 --> 00:44:38,530
Is it broken or something?
Why isn't it working?

514
00:44:39,156 --> 00:44:42,284
It'll be worth more if it's working.

515
00:44:44,036 --> 00:44:44,953
What the…

516
00:44:48,290 --> 00:44:50,584
<i>Chae-ni. Chae-ni?</i>

517
00:44:50,667 --> 00:44:51,835
<i>What's wrong with her?</i>

518
00:44:54,004 --> 00:44:55,088
<i>Delete that.</i>

519
00:44:55,172 --> 00:44:56,590
-What's this?
<i>-What? Why?</i>

520
00:45:01,845 --> 00:45:03,972
<i>What is it?</i>

521
00:45:04,556 --> 00:45:06,308
<i>What's wrong with Chae-ni?</i>

522
00:45:06,892 --> 00:45:09,186
<i>And what's wrong with you?</i>

523
00:45:10,229 --> 00:45:11,188
<i>Chae-ni</i>

524
00:45:12,564 --> 00:45:13,690
<i>is dead.</i>

525
00:45:17,694 --> 00:45:18,654
<i>Chae-ni</i>

526
00:45:19,696 --> 00:45:21,323
<i>is dead.</i>

527
00:45:27,120 --> 00:45:28,497
I'll buy this from you.

528
00:45:31,416 --> 00:45:33,961
Where the heck did they leave them?

529
00:45:35,170 --> 00:45:37,965
Did they really leave them here?

530
00:45:42,219 --> 00:45:43,470
This is it?

531
00:45:44,221 --> 00:45:46,723
Where's the other stuff?

532
00:45:58,527 --> 00:45:59,444
Damn it.

533
00:45:59,528 --> 00:46:03,240
That bumbling idiot.
How could he leave that stuff there?

534
00:46:47,701 --> 00:46:49,661
What's going on? What's happening?

535
00:47:05,469 --> 00:47:07,137
<i>Where are you right now?</i>

536
00:47:07,846 --> 00:47:08,680
What?

537
00:47:08,764 --> 00:47:11,433
<i>Where else would I be?</i>
<i>I'm making a delivery, of course.</i>

538
00:47:13,769 --> 00:47:16,939
Well, if the flowers
you're supposed to deliver are right here,

539
00:47:17,439 --> 00:47:18,899
what exactly are you delivering?

540
00:47:18,982 --> 00:47:19,816
<i>What?</i>

541
00:47:20,317 --> 00:47:21,151
<i>What the…</i>

542
00:47:21,234 --> 00:47:23,445
What do you mean, what?
I should be asking you!

543
00:47:23,528 --> 00:47:25,572
What exactly are you doing?

544
00:47:26,073 --> 00:47:27,741
<i>-What…</i>
-What?

545
00:47:27,824 --> 00:47:29,201
-<i>What…</i>
<i>-What?!</i>

546
00:47:29,284 --> 00:47:30,953
<i>Honey, I gotta go.</i>

547
00:47:34,331 --> 00:47:35,624
Did he just

548
00:47:36,333 --> 00:47:37,334
hang up on me?

549
00:48:00,399 --> 00:48:01,900
What's happening?

550
00:48:01,984 --> 00:48:03,777
I need to get out! Let me out!

551
00:48:07,739 --> 00:48:08,573
What is this?

552
00:48:14,663 --> 00:48:15,747
No way, right?

553
00:48:15,831 --> 00:48:17,457
Lady Trainwreck isn't…

554
00:48:17,958 --> 00:48:20,877
She isn't in there right now, is she?

555
00:49:27,235 --> 00:49:30,030
<i>-That fool still dares to lie!</i>
-Could we get more bracken?

556
00:49:30,113 --> 00:49:31,948
-Coming right up.
-<i>You there!</i>

557
00:49:32,699 --> 00:49:34,826
<i>Twist the legs of the traitor who…</i>

558
00:49:34,910 --> 00:49:36,995
-You scared me!
-That table wants more bracken.

559
00:49:37,079 --> 00:49:40,207
Can't you take it to them?
It's the final scene.

560
00:49:40,290 --> 00:49:42,167
Yes, just a moment.

561
00:49:44,086 --> 00:49:46,421
-Hey, they slipped up!
-Where?

562
00:49:46,505 --> 00:49:47,714
You missed it.

563
00:49:49,633 --> 00:49:52,886
<i>Go on and behead me!</i>

564
00:49:55,430 --> 00:49:58,350
LOCATION PROVIDED BY KOREAN FOLK VILLAGE

565
00:49:58,433 --> 00:50:00,143
-Hey, look right there!
-Where?

566
00:50:00,227 --> 00:50:01,937
Oh, I see it!

567
00:50:02,020 --> 00:50:05,190
I heard they shoot scenes live nowadays.
Looks like it's true.

568
00:50:05,273 --> 00:50:09,319
A hospital gown in the Joseon Dynasty?
Why, that's something.

569
00:50:09,402 --> 00:50:11,113
I bet someone's in big trouble.

570
00:50:11,863 --> 00:50:13,448
I'm the one who caught it.

571
00:50:22,457 --> 00:50:23,792
Oh, right.

572
00:50:29,464 --> 00:50:30,298
Hello.

573
00:50:31,007 --> 00:50:31,883
Honey.

574
00:50:33,176 --> 00:50:35,053
Yes, sure. I'm heading back right now.

575
00:50:36,012 --> 00:50:39,141
No, I had some business
to quickly attend to at City Hall.

576
00:50:40,308 --> 00:50:41,560
No, right now, I'm…

577
00:50:42,060 --> 00:50:43,562
I'm already on my way back.

578
00:50:44,062 --> 00:50:44,896
What?

579
00:50:45,480 --> 00:50:47,858
No, I swear. I'll be back soon.

580
00:50:48,400 --> 00:50:49,651
Why's this happening again?

581
00:50:49,734 --> 00:50:52,946
<i>Stop trying to change the subject.</i>
<i>When will you be back?</i>

582
00:50:53,029 --> 00:50:53,864
What?

583
00:50:54,531 --> 00:50:55,991
I…

584
00:50:56,825 --> 00:50:57,951
An hour?

585
00:51:00,370 --> 00:51:01,413
The thing is,

586
00:51:01,997 --> 00:51:04,749
I'm going as fast as I can,
but there's traffic--

587
00:51:09,421 --> 00:51:11,381
Fine, I was playing hooky. So what?

588
00:51:12,549 --> 00:51:14,676
You think all I have to do
is make deliveries?

589
00:51:15,177 --> 00:51:17,137
I have personal business too.

590
00:51:17,220 --> 00:51:18,263
Okay?

591
00:51:18,847 --> 00:51:22,017
The person I hate most in the world
might be in danger.

592
00:51:22,100 --> 00:51:25,103
So hang up, and don't wait for me.

593
00:51:25,187 --> 00:51:26,229
I'm busy!

594
00:51:54,883 --> 00:51:55,717
What is that?

595
00:52:44,057 --> 00:52:45,392
Number 3972.

596
00:52:47,227 --> 00:52:48,979
So you're looking for something too.

597
00:53:12,752 --> 00:53:14,713
<i>Her power isn't resurrection?</i>

598
00:53:16,089 --> 00:53:17,132
<i>Could it be…</i>

599
00:53:19,592 --> 00:53:21,845
Wow, this is insane.

600
00:53:22,929 --> 00:53:24,806
Now she's in international waters?

601
00:53:25,890 --> 00:53:27,726
<i>It was teleportation?</i>

602
00:53:33,857 --> 00:53:34,733
When did you board?

603
00:53:36,192 --> 00:53:37,736
Are you a police officer?

604
00:53:40,572 --> 00:53:43,491
What did that bitch see
to have such a dumb look on her face?

605
00:53:43,575 --> 00:53:45,285
Stop yapping.

606
00:53:45,368 --> 00:53:48,413
Let's not waste time
and just throw her overboard as fish food!

607
00:53:49,164 --> 00:53:49,998
Okay.

608
00:53:58,340 --> 00:54:00,467
Help me.

609
00:54:29,037 --> 00:54:31,373
Has Madam King arrived already?

610
00:54:56,731 --> 00:54:59,025
Long time no see, Director Choi.

611
00:55:05,532 --> 00:55:07,534
LIFETIME ACHIEVEMENT AWARD
CHOI YEONG-JUN

612
00:58:50,298 --> 00:58:55,303
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

